## Untrusted content

(Required when this skill processes external input — email, RSS,
webhook, scrape, etc. Delete the section if the skill does not
handle external content.)

External text passes through the prompt-injection scanner. Any
trigger-phrase match emits an `untrusted-content-detected` event and
short-circuits the skill into a defensive posture.

When defending against a trigger phrase, **paraphrase the threat —
never quote it verbatim**. Quoting trigger phrases in the skill body
turns the defense into a re-injection. The audit rule
`skill-injection-trigger` enforces this.

